p: TERRITORY OF WASHINGTON, County of Spokane } SS. Territory of Washington, Plaintiff vs. S.P. White, Defendant } In the District Court of the Territory of Washington and for the Lincoln Judicial District thereof, holding terms at Cheney, Spokane County, in said Territory To the Sheriff of Spokane Lincoln County, Greeting: IN THE NAME OF THE UNITED STATES, You are hereby commanded to summon Ehuer Warren Eva Stephey to be and appear before the District Court aforesaid at the Court House, in Cheney, in said County, on the forthwith day of A.D. 1885, at o'clock, M. to there give evi- dence in the above entitiled cause on the part of said Defendant S.P. White Witness the Hon. George Turner Associate Judge of the Supreme Court of Washington Territory, and Judge of said Court, and the Seal there- of affixed, this 17 day of April A.D. 1885 Kate W. Feauerbach Clerk. By R. Dtrobach Deputy.
